# PC Time Limit Application - Project Overview

This is a parental control application that allows parents to limit PC time for their children. The application consists of three main components:

## Architecture Overview

### 1. Time Limit App (Child PC)
- **Location**: [PCTimeLimit/](mdc:PCTimeLimit/)
- **Type**: WPF application installed on child's PC
- **Purpose**: Enforces time limits, tracks usage, communicates with server
- **Key Files**:
  - [MainWindow.xaml](mdc:PCTimeLimit/MainWindow.xaml) - Main UI for child
  - [SettingsWindow.xaml](mdc:PCTimeLimit/SettingsWindow.xaml) - Child settings
  - [StatsWindow.xaml](mdc:PCTimeLimit/StatsWindow.xaml) - Usage statistics

### 2. Admin Time Limit App (Parent PC)
- **Location**: [PCTimeLimitAdmin/](mdc:PCTimeLimitAdmin/)
- **Type**: WPF application installed on parent's PC
- **Purpose**: Configure time limits, monitor usage, manage child accounts
- **Key Files**:
  - [MainWindow.xaml](mdc:PCTimeLimitAdmin/MainWindow.xaml) - Parent control panel
  - [LoginWindow.xaml](mdc:PCTimeLimitAdmin/LoginWindow.xaml) - Parent authentication
  - [Services/TcpClientService.cs](mdc:PCTimeLimitAdmin/Services/TcpClientService.cs) - Server communication
  - [Shared/MessageProtocol.cs](mdc:PCTimeLimitAdmin/Shared/MessageProtocol.cs) - Communication protocol

### 3. Server (24/7 Running PC)
- **Location**: [PCTimeLimitServer/](mdc:PCTimeLimitServer/)
- **Type**: Custom server application
- **Purpose**: Handle connections between parent and child PCs, manage accounts
- **Key Files**:
  - [Program.cs](mdc:PCTimeLimitServer/Program.cs) - Server entry point
  - [AccountManager.cs](mdc:PCTimeLimitServer/AccountManager.cs) - User account management

## Communication Flow
1. Parent configures time limits via Admin App
2. Admin App sends configuration to Server via TCP
3. Server stores configuration and manages accounts
4. Child PC connects to Server to receive time limit settings
5. Child PC enforces limits locally and reports usage back to Server
6. Parent can monitor usage through Admin App

## Development Guidelines
- Use WPF for desktop applications
- Implement secure TCP communication between components
- Store configuration and usage data on the server
- Ensure child PC cannot bypass time limits
- Provide real-time monitoring capabilities for parents
